# üìß CA02 ‚Äî Spam Email Classification & Model Evaluation

---

## üìå Overview
This project builds a machine learning model that classifies emails as **Spam** or **Ham (Not Spam)** using a **Gaussian Naive Bayes classifier**.

The assignment demonstrates a complete NLP pipeline:

1. Load raw text emails  
2. Clean and preprocess text  
3. Convert text into numerical features  
4. Train a classifier  
5. Evaluate prediction performance

---

## üìÇ Dataset Structure
```
CA02/
‚îÇ
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ TRAIN/   -> Training emails
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ TEST/    -> Testing emails
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ CA02.ipynb
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ README.md
```

Each file represents a single labeled email message.

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è Methodology

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Data Loading
- Read all email files from directories
- Combine lines into a single email body
- Assign labels based on folder location

---

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Text Preprocessing
Noise is removed before modeling:

- Lowercase conversion
- Remove punctuation & numbers
- Remove stopwords
- Remove single-character words

---

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ Feature Engineering (Bag-of-Words)
A dictionary is built from the most frequent words in the training set.

| Step | Description |
|----|------|
| Build Dictionary | Select most frequent words |
| Count Occurrences | Word frequency per email |
| Feature Matrix | Emails ‚Üí Numerical vectors |

Rows = Emails  
Columns = Word counts

---

### 4Ô∏è‚É£ Model Training
A **Gaussian Naive Bayes** classifier is trained.

The algorithm learns probability distributions of words appearing in spam vs non-spam emails.

---

### 5Ô∏è‚É£ Prediction
The trained model predicts labels for unseen emails in the test dataset.

---

### 6Ô∏è‚É£ Model Evaluation
Performance is measured using classification metrics:

| Metric | Purpose |
|------|------|
| Accuracy | Overall correctness |
| Precision | Correct spam predictions |
| Recall | Ability to detect spam |
| F1 Score | Balance of precision & recall |
| Confusion Matrix | Detailed prediction breakdown |

---

## üìä Example Output
```
reading and processing emails from TRAIN and TEST folders
